.TH "blk_alloc_devt" 9 "blk_alloc_devt" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
blk_alloc_devt \- allocate a dev_t for a block device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" blk_alloc_devt
.BI "(struct block_device *bdev "  ","
.BI "dev_t *devt "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bdev" 12
block device to allocate dev_t for
.IP "devt" 12
out parameter for resulting dev_t
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate a dev_t for block device.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, allocated dev_t is returned in *\fIdevt\fP.  -errno on
failure.
.SH "CONTEXT"
Might sleep.
